name: Rowlet
flavorText: At a distance, it launches its sharp feathers while flying about. If the enemy gets too close, Rowlet switches tactics and delivers vicious kicks.
Ability1Text: If you played Bird Keeper from your hand during this turn, ignore all Energy in this Pokemon's attack costs.
Attack1Text: This attack does 60 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Dartrix
flavorText: It throws one knifelike feather after another at its enemies, and each one precisely strikes a weak point. These feathers are known as blade quills.

name: Decidueye
flavorText: As if wielding a bow, it launches the arrow quills hidden among the feathers of its wings. Decidueye's shots never miss.
Ability1Text: Prevent all damage done to this Pokemon by attacks from your opponent's Pokemon V and Pokemon-GX.
Attack1Text: This attack also does 20 damage to 2 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Grookey
flavorText: When it uses its special stick to strike up a beat, the sound waves produced carry revitalizing energy to the plants and flowers in the area.
Attack1Text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 10 damage for each heads.

name: Thwackey
flavorText: The faster a Thwackey can beat out a rhythm with its two sticks, the more respect it wins from its peers.
Ability1Text: If you have a Stadium in play, this Pokemon has no Retreat Cost.

name: Rillaboom
flavorText: By drumming, it taps into the power of its special tree stump. The roots of the stump follow its direction in battle.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may search your deck for up to 2 Grass Energy cards and attach them to 1 of your Pokemon. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Blipbug
flavorText: Often found in gardens, this Pokemon has hairs on its body that it uses to assess its surroundings.

name: Dottler
flavorText: As it grows inside its shell, it uses its psychic abilities to monitor the outside world and prepare for evolution.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokemon takes 40 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Orbeetle
flavorText: It emits psychic energy to observe and study what's around it—and what's around it can include things over six miles away.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may look at the top 3 cards of your opponent's deck and put them back in any order.
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 more damage for each Psychic Energy attached to this Pokemon.

name: Gossifleur
flavorText: It whirls around in the wind while singing a joyous song. This delightful display has charmed many into raising this Pokemon.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 3 Basic Pokemon and put them onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Eldegoss
flavorText: The cotton on the head of this Pokemon can be spun into a glossy, gorgeous yarn—a Galar regional specialty.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 3 Grass Energy cards and attach them to your Benched Pokemon in any way you like. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Applin
flavorText: It spends its entire life inside an apple. It hides from its natural enemies, bird Pokemon, by pretending it's just an apple and nothing more.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage done to this Pokemon by attacks.

name: Flapple
flavorText: It ate a sour apple, and that induced its evolution. In its cheeks, it stores an acid capable of causing chemical burns.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may put 2 damage counters on 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. If you placed any damage counters in this way, shuffle this Pokemon and all attached cards into your deck.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Appletun
flavorText: Eating a sweet apple caused its evolution. A nectarous scent wafts from its body, luring in the bug Pokemon it preys on.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may flip a coin. If heads, switch 1 of your opponent's Benched Basic Pokemon with their Active Pokemon.

name: Scorbunny
flavorText: It has special pads on the backs of its feet, and one on its nose. Once it's raring to fight, these pads radiate tremendous heat.
Attack1Text: Discard an Energy from this Pokemon.

name: Raboot
flavorText: It kicks berries right off the branches of trees and then juggles them with its feet, practicing its footwork.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Fire Energy card and attach it to this Pokemon. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Cinderace
flavorText: It's skilled at both offense and defense, and it gets pumped up when cheered on. But if it starts showboating, it could put itself in a tough spot.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, when this Pokemon moves from your Bench to the Active Spot, you may attach up to 2 Fire Energy cards from your discard pile to it.
Attack1Text: Discard 2 Energy from this Pokemon.

name: Sizzlipede
flavorText: It stores flammable gas in its body and uses it to generate heat. The yellow sections on its belly get particularly hot.

name: Centiskorch
flavorText: When it heats up, its body temperature reaches about 1,500 degrees Fahrenheit. It lashes its body like a whip and launches itself at enemies.
Attack1Text: For each Fire Energy attached to this Pokemon, discard the top card of your opponent's deck.
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Burned.

name: Galarian Mr. Mime
flavorText: Its talent is tap-dancing. It can also manipulate temperatures to create a floor of ice, which this Pokemon can kick up to use as a barrier.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokemon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Galarian Mr. Rime
flavorText: It's highly skilled at tap-dancing. It waves its cane of ice in time with its graceful movements.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may switch 1 of your opponent's face-down Prize cards with the top card of their deck. (The cards stay face down.)
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 damage for each Pokemon in your discard pile that has the Mad Party attack.

name: Suicune
flavorText: Said to be the embodiment of north winds, it can instantly purify filthy, murky water.
Attack2Text: Put 2 Water Energy attached to this Pokemon into your hand.

name: Galarian Darumaka
flavorText: It lived in snowy areas for so long that its fire sac cooled off and atrophied. It now has an organ that generates cold instead.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Galarian Darmanitan
flavorText: On days when blizzards blow through, it comes down to where people live. It stashes food in the snowball on its head, taking it home for later.
Attack1Text: This attack also does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)
Attack2Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon can't use Crushing Headbutt.

name: Sobble
flavorText: When scared, this Pokemon cries. Its tears pack the chemical punch of 100 onions, and attackers won't be able to resist weeping.

name: Drizzile
flavorText: A clever combatant, this Pokemon battles using water balloons created with moisture secreted from its palms.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokemon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokemon during your turn, you may search your deck for up to 2 Trainer cards, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Inteleon
flavorText: It has many hidden capabilities, such as fingertips that can shoot water and a membrane on its back that it can use to glide through the air.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokemon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokemon during your turn, you may search your deck for up to 2 Trainer cards, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack1Text: This attack also does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Chewtle
flavorText: It starts off battles by attacking with its rock-hard horn, but as soon as the opponent flinches, this Pokemon bites down and never lets go.

name: Drednaw
flavorText: This Pokemon rapidly extends its retractable neck to sink its sharp fangs into distant enemies and take them down.
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 more damage for each Colorless in your opponent's Active Pokemon's Retreat Cost.
Attack2Text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokemon can't retreat.

name: Cramorant
flavorText: It's so strong that it can knock out some opponents in a single hit, but it also may forget what it's battling midfight.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to this Pokemon.
Attack2Text: This attack does 20 more damage for each Water Energy attached to this Pokemon.

name: Arrokuda
flavorText: If it sees any movement around it, this Pokemon charges for it straightaway, leading with its sharply pointed jaw. It's very proud of that jaw.

name: Barraskewda
flavorText: This Pokemon has a jaw that's as sharp as a spear and as strong as steel. Apparently Barraskewda's flesh is surprisingly tasty, too.
Attack2Text: Discard 2 Water Energy cards from your hand. If you don't, this attack does nothing.

name: Snom
flavorText: It spits out thread imbued with a frigid sort of energy and uses it to tie its body to branches, disguising itself as an icicle while it sleeps.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Basic Pokemon and put it onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Frosmoth
flavorText: It shows no mercy to any who desecrate fields and mountains. It will fly around on its icy wings, causing a blizzard to chase offenders away.
Ability1Text: As often as you like during your turn, you may attach a Water Energy card from your hand to 1 of your Benched Water Pokemon.

name: Eiscue
flavorText: It drifted in on the flow of ocean waters from a frigid place. It keeps its head iced constantly to make sure it stays nice and cold.
Ability1Text: If this Pokemon has full HP, it takes 60 less damage from your opponent's attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack1Text: This attack also does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Dracovish
flavorText: Powerful legs and jaws made it the apex predator of its time. Its own overhunting of its prey was what drove it to extinction.
Ability1Text: As long as this Pokemon is in the Active Spot, your opponent can't play any Pokemon from their hand to evolve their Pokemon.

name: Arctovish
flavorText: Though it's able to capture prey by freezing its surroundings, it has trouble eating the prey afterward because its mouth is on top of its head.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokemon takes 60 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Asleep.

name: Rotom
flavorText: One boy's invention led to the development of many different machines that take advantage of Rotom's unique capabilities.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokemon from your hand onto your Bench during your turn, you may search your deck for up to 2 Item cards that have the word "Rotom" in their name, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Yamper
flavorText: This Pokemon is very popular as a herding dog in the Galar region. As it runs, it generates electricity from the base of its tail.
Attack1Text: Your opponent switches their Active Pokemon with 1 of their Benched Pokemon.

name: Boltund
flavorText: This Pokemon generates electricity and channels it into its legs to keep them going strong. Boltund can run nonstop for three full days.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokemon can't retreat.
Attack2Text: If your opponent's Active Pokemon is a Pokemon V or Pokemon-GX, this attack does 90 more damage.

name: Toxel
flavorText: It stores poison in an internal poison sac and secretes that poison through its skin. If you touch this Pokemon, a tingling sensation follows.

name: Toxtricity
flavorText: When this Pokemon sounds as if it's strumming a guitar, it's actually clawing at the protrusions on its chest to generate electricity.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard the top 5 cards of your opponent's deck. If tails, discard the top 5 cards of your deck.
Attack2Text: This Pokemon also does 30 damage to itself.

name: Pincurchin
flavorText: It feeds on seaweed, using its teeth to scrape it off rocks. Electric current flows from the tips of its spines.
Attack1Text: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 30 damage for each heads. If at least 2 of them are heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Morpeko
flavorText: As it eats the seeds stored up in its pocket-like pouches, this Pokemon is not just satisfying its constant hunger. It's also generating electricity.
Attack1Text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Active Pokemon's attacks. During your opponent's next turn, that Pokemon can't use that attack.
Attack2Text: This attack also does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Dracozolt
flavorText: In ancient times, it was unbeatable thanks to its powerful lower body, but it went extinct anyway after it depleted all its plant-based food sources.
Attack1Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon's Amping Up attack does 90 more damage (before applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack2Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon can't attack.

name: Arctozolt
flavorText: The shaking of its freezing upper half is what generates its electricity. It has a hard time walking around.
Ability1Text: Whenever your opponent attaches an Energy card from their hand to 1 of their Pokemon, put 2 damage counters on that Pokemon.

name: Galarian Ponyta
flavorText: This Pokemon will look into your eyes and read the contents of your heart. If it finds evil there, it promptly hides away.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Galarian Rapidash
flavorText: Brave and prideful, this Pokemon dashes airily through the forest, its steps aided by the psychic power stored in the fur on its fetlocks.
Ability1Text: Your Pokemon recover from all Special Conditions and can't be affected by any Special Conditions.
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 more damage for each Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Galarian Corsola
flavorText: Watch your step when wandering areas oceans once covered. What looks like a stone could be this Pokemon, and it will curse you if you kick it.
Attack1Text: Put 3 damage counters on your opponent's Pokemon in any way you like.

name: Galarian Cursola
flavorText: Its shell is overflowing with its heightened otherworldly energy. The ectoplasm serves as protection for this Pokemon's core spirit.
Ability1Text: If this Pokemon is in the Active Spot and is Knocked Out by damage from an opponent's attack, flip a coin. If heads, the Attacking Pokemon is Knocked Out.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokemon can't retreat.

name: Dedenne
flavorText: Its upper whiskers are sensors that survey its surroundings. Its lower whiskers are organs that shoot electricity.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 damage for each Pokemon in your discard pile that has the Mad Party attack.

name: Sinistea
flavorText: This Pokemon is said to have been born when a lonely spirit possessed a cold, leftover cup of tea.
Attack1Text: Put 2 damage counters on your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Polteageist
flavorText: This species lives in antique teapots. Most pots are forgeries, but on rare occasions, an authentic work is found.
Ability1Text: You must discard a Pokemon that has the Mad Party attack from your hand in order to use this Ability. Once during your turn, you may draw 2 cards.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 damage for each Pokemon in your discard pile that has the Mad Party attack.

name: Hatenna
flavorText: Via the protrusion on its head, it senses other creatures' emotions. If you don't have a calm disposition, it will never warm up to you.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Pokemon, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Hattrem
flavorText: No matter who you are, if you bring strong emotions near this Pokemon, it will silence you violently.
Attack1Text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage.

name: Hatterene
flavorText: It emits psychic power strong enough to cause headaches as a deterrent to the approach of others.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may use this Ability. Each player discards a card from their hand. (Your opponent discards first.)
Attack1Text: Put 1 damage counter on your opponent's Active Pokemon for each Pokemon in your discard pile.

name: Milcery
flavorText: This Pokemon was born from sweet-smelling particles in the air. Its body is made of cream.
Attack1Text: Heal 10 damage from each of your Pokemon.

name: Alcremie
flavorText: When it trusts a Trainer, it will treat them to berries it's decorated with cream.
Attack1Text: Attach any number of basic Energy cards from your hand to your Pokemon in any way you like.
Attack2Text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokemon.

name: Indeedee
flavorText: These intelligent Pokemon touch horns with each other to share information between them.
Attack1Text: Heal 30 damage from each of your Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Confused.

name: Dreepy
flavorText: After being reborn as a ghost Pokemon, Dreepy wanders the areas it used to inhabit back when it was alive in prehistoric seas.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 more damage.

name: Drakloak
flavorText: It's capable of flying faster than 120 mph. It battles alongside Dreepy and dotes on them until they successfully evolve.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Dreepy and put it onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Dragapult
flavorText: When it isn't battling, it keeps Dreepy in the holes on its horns. Once a fight starts, it launches the Dreepy like supersonic missiles.
Ability1Text: If any damage is done to this Pokemon by attacks, flip a coin. If heads, prevent that damage.
Attack1Text: Put 3 damage counters on your opponent's Benched Pokemon in any way you like.

name: Galarian Farfetch'd
flavorText: The Farfetch'd of the Galar region are brave warriors, and they wield thick, tough leeks in battle.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage.

name: Galarian Sirfetch'd
flavorText: Only Farfetch'd that have survived many battles can attain this evolution. When this Pokemon's leek withers, it will retire from combat.
Attack2Text: This Pokemon can't use Meteor Assault again until it leaves the Active Spot.

name: Galarian Yamask
flavorText: A clay slab with cursed engravings took possession of a Yamask. The slab is said to be absorbing the Yamask's dark power.
Attack1Text: This Pokemon also does 30 damage to itself.

name: Galarian Runerigus
flavorText: A powerful curse was woven into an ancient painting. After absorbing the spirit of a Yamask, the painting began to move.
Attack1Text: For each damage counter on this Galarian Runerigus, put 2 damage counters on your opponent's Pokemon in any way you like.
Attack2Text: This Pokemon also does 30 damage to itself.

name: Rolycoly
flavorText: Most of its body has the same composition as coal. Fittingly, this Pokemon was first discovered in coal mines about 400 years ago.

name: Carkol
flavorText: It forms coal inside its body. Coal dropped by this Pokemon once helped fuel the lives of people in the Galar region.

name: Coalossal
flavorText: It's usually peaceful, but the vandalism of mines enrages it. Offenders will be incinerated with flames that reach 2,700 degrees Fahrenheit.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may attach a Fire Energy card, a Fighting Energy card, or 1 of each from your discard pile to your Pokemon in any way you like.

name: Silicobra
flavorText: It spews sand from its nostrils. While the enemy is blinded, it burrows into the ground to hide.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, if the Defending Pokemon tries to attack, your opponent flips a coin. If tails, that attack doesn't happen.

name: Sandaconda
flavorText: Its unique style of coiling allows it to blast sand out of its sand sac more efficiently.
Attack1Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon's attacks do 120 more damage to your opponent's Active Pokemon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Clobbopus
flavorText: It's very curious, but its means of investigating things is to try to punch them with its tentacles. The search for food is what brings it onto land.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Grapploct
flavorText: A body made up of nothing but muscle makes the grappling moves this Pokemon performs with its tentacles tremendously powerful.
Attack1Text: Until this Grapploct leaves the Active Spot, the Defending Pokemon's attacks cost ColorlessColorless more, and the Defending Pokemon can't retreat. This effect can't be applied more than once.
Attack2Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Resistance.

name: Falinks
flavorText: Five of them are troopers, and one is the brass. The brass's orders are absolute.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 Basic Pokemon and put them onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: This attack does 30 damage for each of your Benched Pokemon that has "Falinks" in its name.

name: Stonjourner
flavorText: It stands in grasslands, watching the sun's descent from zenith to horizon. This Pokemon has a talent for delivering dynamic kicks.
Attack2Text: If this Pokemon has at least 1 extra Energy attached (in addition to this attack's cost), this attack does 60 more damage.

name: Koffing
flavorText: Its body is full of poisonous gas. It floats into garbage dumps, seeking out the fumes of raw, rotting trash.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a card that evolves from this Pokemon and put it onto this Pokemon to evolve it. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Galarian Weezing
flavorText: This Pokemon consumes particles that contaminate the air. Instead of leaving droppings, it expels clean air.
Ability1Text: As long as this Pokemon is in the Active Spot, your opponent's Pokemon in play have no Abilities, except for Neutralizing Gas.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Poisoned. Put 4 damage counters instead of 1 on that Pokemon during Pokemon Checkup.

name: Galarian Zigzagoon
flavorText: Thought to be the oldest form of Zigzagoon, it moves in zigzags and wreaks havoc upon its surroundings.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokemon from your hand onto your Bench during your turn, you may put 1 damage counter on 1 of your opponent's Pokemon.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Galarian Linoone
flavorText: This very aggressive Pokemon will recklessly challenge opponents stronger than itself.
Attack1Text: Switch this Pokemon with 1 of your Benched Pokemon.

name: Galarian Obstagoon
flavorText: It evolved after experiencing numerous fights. While crossing its arms, it lets out a shout that would make any opponent flinch.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokemon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokemon during your turn, you may put 3 damage counters on 1 of your opponent's Pokemon.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage done to this Pokemon by attacks from Basic Pokemon.

name: Nickit
flavorText: Aided by the soft pads on its feet, it silently raids the food stores of other Pokemon. It survives off its ill-gotten gains.
Attack1Text: Your opponent shuffles their hand and puts it on the bottom of their deck. If they put any cards on the bottom of their deck in this way, they draw 3 cards.

name: Thievul
flavorText: It secretly marks potential targets with a scent. By following the scent, it stalks its targets and steals from them when they least expect it.
Attack1Text: Your opponent reveals their hand. Choose a card you find there and put it on the bottom of their deck.

name: Impidimp
flavorText: Through its nose, it sucks in the emanations produced by people and Pokemon when they feel annoyed. It thrives off this negative energy.

name: Morgrem
flavorText: When it gets down on all fours as if to beg for forgiveness, it's trying to lure opponents in so that it can stab them with its spear-like hair.
Attack2Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by any effects on your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Grimmsnarl
flavorText: With the hair wrapped around its body helping to enhance its muscles, this Pokemon can overwhelm even Machamp.
Ability1Text: As long as this Pokemon is in the Active Spot, your opponent's Active Pokemon's attacks cost Colorless more.
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 more damage for each Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Galarian Meowth
flavorText: Living with a savage, seafaring people has toughened this Pokemon's body so much that parts of it have turned to iron.
Ability1Text: You must discard 2 cards from your hand in order to use this Ability. Once during your turn, you may search your deck for a Galarian Perrserker, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Galarian Perrserker
flavorText: What appears to be an iron helmet is actually hardened hair. This Pokemon lives for the thrill of battle.
Ability1Text: Your Metal Pokemon's attacks do 20 more damage to your opponent's Active Pokemon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Galarian Stunfisk
flavorText: Living in mud with a high iron content has given it a strong steel body.
Ability1Text: If this Pokemon is in the Active Spot and is damaged by an opponent's attack (even if it is Knocked Out), discard an Energy from the Attacking Pokemon.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 30 more damage for each heads.

name: Corviknight
flavorText: This Pokemon reigns supreme in the skies of the Galar region. The black luster of its steel body could drive terror into the heart of any foe.
Attack2Text: You may discard 2 Energy from this Pokemon. If you do, during your opponent's next turn, this Pokemon takes 100 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Cufant
flavorText: It digs up the ground with its trunk. It's also very strong, being able to carry loads of over five tons without any problem at all.

name: Copperajah
flavorText: They came over from another region long ago and worked together with humans. Their green skin is resistant to water.
Ability1Text: This Pokemon can't be affected by any Special Conditions.
Attack1Text: If your Benched Pokemon have any damage counters on them, this attack does 120 more damage.

name: Duraludon
flavorText: Its body resembles polished metal, and it's both lightweight and strong. The only drawback is that it rusts easily.
Attack1Text: Attach a Metal Energy card from your discard pile to 1 of your Pokemon.

name: Minccino
flavorText: The way it brushes away grime with its tail can be helpful when cleaning. But its focus on spotlessness can make cleaning more of a hassle.
Attack1Text: Look at the top card of your opponent's deck.
Attack2Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 damage for each heads.

name: Cinccino
flavorText: Its body secretes oil that this Pokemon spreads over its nest as a coating to protect it from dust. Cinccino won't tolerate even a speck of the stuff.
Ability1Text: You must discard a card from your hand in order to use this Ability. Once during your turn, you may draw 2 cards.
Attack1Text: Attach a basic Energy card from your discard pile to 1 of your Benched Pokemon.

name: Ducklett
flavorText: They are better at swimming than flying, and they happily eat their favorite food, peat moss, as they dive underwater.

name: Swanna
flavorText: Swanna start to dance at dusk. The one dancing in the middle is the leader of the flock.
Ability1Text: If you played Bird Keeper from your hand during this turn, ignore all Energy in this Pokemon's attack costs.
Attack1Text: You may discard a card from your hand. If you do, this attack does 70 more damage.

name: Bunnelby
flavorText: It excels at digging holes. Using its ears, it can dig a nest 33 feet deep in one night.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 damage for each Pokemon in your discard pile that has the Mad Party attack.

name: Oranguru
flavorText: It knows the forest inside and out. If it comes across a wounded Pokemon, Oranguru will gather medicinal herbs to treat it.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may switch a card from your hand with the top card of your deck.

name: Skwovet
flavorText: Found throughout the Galar region, this Pokemon becomes uneasy if its cheeks are ever completely empty of berries.

name: Greedent
flavorText: It stashes berries in its tail—so many berries that they fall out constantly. But this Pokemon is a bit slow-witted, so it doesn't notice the loss.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may search your deck for a Pokemon Tool card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Rookidee
flavorText: It will bravely challenge any opponent, no matter how powerful. This Pokemon benefits from every battle—even a defeat increases its strength a bit.

name: Corvisquire
flavorText: Smart enough to use tools in battle, these Pokemon have been seen picking up rocks and flinging them or using ropes to wrap up enemies.
Attack1Text: Before doing damage, discard all Pokemon Tools from your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Wooloo
flavorText: If its fleece grows too long, Wooloo won't be able to move. Cloth made with the wool of this Pokemon is surprisingly strong.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokemon takes 10 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Dubwool
flavorText: Its majestic horns are meant only to impress the opposite gender. They never see use in battle.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokemon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack2Text: This Pokemon also does 30 damage to itself.

name: Rillaboom V
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 Basic Grass Pokemon and put them onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: This Pokemon also does 30 damage to itself.

name: Rillaboom VMAX
Attack2Text: You may discard up to 3 Grass Energy from this Pokemon. If you do, this attack does 50 more damage for each card you discarded in this way.

name: Charizard VMAX
Attack2Text: Discard 2 Energy from this Pokemon.

name: Centiskorch V
Attack1Text: You may discard an Energy from this Pokemon. If you do, discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Centiskorch VMAX
Attack1Text: This attack does 40 more damage for each Fire Energy attached to this Pokemon. If you did any damage with this attack, you may attach a Fire Energy card from your discard pile to this Pokemon.

name: Lapras V
Attack1Text: Attach a Water Energy card from your hand to this Pokemon. If you do, switch it with 1 of your Benched Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Put 2 Water Energy attached to this Pokemon into your hand.

name: Lapras VMAX
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 more damage for each Water Energy attached to this Pokemon.

name: Toxtricity V
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Poisoned.
Attack2Text: If your opponent's Active Pokemon is Poisoned, this attack does 90 more damage.

name: Toxtricity VMAX
Attack1Text: If your opponent's Active Pokemon is Poisoned, this attack does 80 more damage.

name: Indeedee V
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may heal 20 damage from your Active Pokemon.
Attack1Text: This attack does 60 more damage for each Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Falinks V
Ability1Text: All of your Pokemon that have "Falinks" in their name take 20 less damage from your opponent's attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack1Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon can't attack.

name: Grimmsnarl V
Attack2Text: Put 2 Darkness Energy attached to this Pokemon into your hand.

name: Grimmsnarl VMAX
Attack1Text: This attack does 50 more damage for each extra Darkness Energy attached to this Pokemon (in addition to this attack's cost). You can't add more than 100 damage in this way.

name: Ditto V
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may choose a Basic Pokemon V from your discard pile and switch it with this Pokemon. Any attached cards, damage counters, Special Conditions, turns in play, and any other effects remain on the new Pokemon.
Attack1Text: Attach a basic Energy card from your discard pile to this Pokemon.

name: Ditto VMAX
Attack1Text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Active Pokemon's attacks and use it as this attack.

name: Dubwool V
Ability1Text: This Pokemon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 more damage for each Prize card your opponent has taken.

name: Eternatus V
Attack1Text: You may attach a Darkness Energy card from your hand to 1 of your Benched Pokemon.
Attack2Text: If your opponent's Active Pokemon is a Pokemon VMAX, this attack does 120 more damage.

name: Eternatus VMAX
Ability1Text: If all of your Pokemon in play are Darkness type, you can have up to 8 Pokemon on your Bench, and you can't put non-Darkness Pokemon into play. (If this Ability stops working, discard Pokemon from your Bench until you have 5.)
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 damage for each of your Darkness Pokemon in play.
